reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a beautiful, unique book shelf for a small space. I fit quite a lot of paperbacks on it and the drawer was larger than I thought it would be. You can get approximately 9 paperbacks on each shelf, depending on the size of the book. Assembly wasn't too bad, but I did have to get a drill to screw in some on the backboard. The holes weren't deep enough. Very happy with it.

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Very nice bookcase. I love the style of it and the color I purchased. It’s going to go perfect with my living room once it all comes together. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Significant lean & wobble with weight of books
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this shelf in mid-2022, and have been using it for almost ~1 year. It is a good looking, polished product. The assembly is slightly tedious-- there are a lot of screws to hand tighten, as others have mentioned-- but nothing unmanageable and the instructions were fine.The main issue is that the primary load-bearing structure of the shelf is a thin & surprisingly flimsy board on the back of the tree structure (against the wall). What's worse-- it isn't even a solid piece all the way up, but rather two halves joined together at the edges by two tiny screws & dowels, half way up the height of the shelf. The result: after ~1 year of use, the shelf wobbles a lot and has developed a significant lean forward of ~4-5 inches at the top (away from the wall). When newly assembled, the top back of the shelf was within 1 inch of the wall. The base of the shelf was never moved, so the ~3-4 inches of lean developed over ~1 year with the weight of the books.From the beginning, the shelf has been only ~50% filled with books, and all the heavier hardcovers are on the bottom 3-4 shelves. The top half of the shelf only has relatively light items & souvenirs. Also, we have always been very careful to push the books all the way back on the shelf (towards to wall), so the weight would be closest to the support. And yet there is still a significant forward lean & wobble. I can't imagine what would happen if the entire shelf was filled with books, from top to bottom!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice quality shelf with a neat retro/vintage feel
reviews.reviewText: I assembled this shelf last night for my 8-track tape collection, and it fits the retro vibe I'm going for really well! Love the diagonal/angular look with the woodgrain finish. There's a nostalgic charm factor to it that is hard to really describe correctly.The only issue I really had with it is that because of its design, it actually doesn't hold quite as much as I thought it would. I was able to fit all 82 of my tapes on it, but just barely. Not a big deal, because I'm re-arranging/trying to purge some stuff in my finished basement anyway. The drawer, although small-looking, actually holds a decent number of items comfortably, so that helped alleviate my concern about the capacity.All in all, this is a beautiful, stylish shelf that I would absolutely recommend for anyone looking to add a retro feel to their living space. :)
This is a cute stylish book rack. Takes less space but can accommodate many books. I loved the quality.

Got it for my kids gaming stuff and books as we are book-dragons family and lacking shelves despite almost whole room dedicated to library. Extremely easy and fast to build and relatively solid although because of shape a bit wobbly so need to be attached to wall for safety. Fit nicely between our display cabinet and bookshelf in living room where was hardly 20inches space. Got also the small version for my nightstand and finally have order with my "relaxing" books :)

reviews.reviewTitle: Nice stand, tricky to put together
reviews.reviewText: The instructions are, well, meh. Once you figure out the way the shelves run and how the screws go in, it's fine. Suggest if able to carefully use a screw gun with appropriate Allen key type bit as doing all of it by hand is tedious and will wreck your thumbs after awhile.

This thing is awesome! I use it to hold my coloring books. Its fun looking, holds stuff great, it does need mounted to the wall as it is unsturdy but it comes with the mount and I actually have not mounted it yet and I am not fearful of it falling currently. Nice piece of furniture that many will comment on. Doesn't need much space. Sorry camera broken or I would post a pic,
